      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "**Data Integrity and Storage Overview**\n\nThe DataStream DB engine is designed to maintain the highest levels of data integrity and storage efficiency, ensuring that all data is accurately stored and retrieved while minimizing latency and maximizing throughput. To achieve this, the engine employs a robust storage engine that leverages advanced techniques such as write-ahead logging (WAL) and write-intensive optimization to ensure that all data is written to disk in a consistent and reliable manner.\n\nThe engine's storage engine is built on top of a sharded, distributed architecture that utilizes a combination of B-Trees and index structures to optimize data retrieval and storage. This architecture enables the engine to scale horizontally, supporting large workloads and high levels of concurrency while maintaining consistency and availability. The engine's metadata management system ensures that all data is properly normalized and partitioned, minimizing data redundancy and improving query performance.\n\nTo ensure data integrity, the engine employs a range of concurrency control mechanisms, including locking and transactional isolation levels, to prevent deadlocks and ensure that all data is consistent across the system. The engine also utilizes a checkpointing mechanism to ensure that all data is properly flushed to disk in the event of a failure, minimizing data loss and ensuring that the system can recover quickly from any errors. By",
